Natali Castellanos-Tyler, 30, was killed in an SUV crash February 21 in Virginia . 
  Her daughter Elisa Tyler has been having nightmares and daytime visions about a white van . 
  Police said the crash was a one-car collision caused by a rain-soaked road . 
  The married mother of three was returning home from a birthday party when her Ford Explorer ran off the road and slammed into a tree . 
  Her husband Craig Tyler believes the white van may have been involved in three hit-and-run incidents in the area . 
 